"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"  # Security\\n\\n  ## Security Claims\\n\\n  A verified zphoto provides the following guarantees:\\n\\n  1. **Device Authenticity**: The photo was signed on a genuine Apple device with a Secure Enclave\\n  2. **App Binding**: The signing key is bound to a specific application via Apple App Attest\\n  3. **Content Integrity**: The photo has not been modified since the signature was created\\n  4. **Proof Validity**: The above properties are verified in a zero-knowledge proof that chains to Apple's root certificate\\n\\n  ## Trust Assumptions\\n\\n  The security of ZCAM relies on the following assumptions:\\n\\n  | Assumption | Rationale |\\n  |------------|-----------|\\n  | Secure Enclave keys cannot be exfiltrated | Hardware security guarantee from Apple |\\n  | Apple App Attest is honest | Apple signs attestations only for legitimate device/app pairs |\\n  | SP1 proof system is sound | Groth16 proofs cannot be forged without the witness |\\n  | SDK code integrity | The SDK code on-device has not been tampered with |\\n\\n  ## Threat Model\\n\\n  ### In Scope\\n  - **AI-generated images**: Attacker attempts to prove a synthetic image as authentic\\n  - **Edited photos**: Attacker modifies a photo after capture and claims it's original\\n  - **Replay attacks**: Attacker reuses attestation/assertion from a different photo\\n  - **Malicious third-party apps**: An app using the SDK attempts to sign non-camera images\\n\\n  ### Out of Scope\\n  - **Compromised device**: Jailbroken devices or hardware attacks on Secure Enclave\\n  - **Apple as adversary**: We trust Apple's attestation service\\n  - **Proof system attacks**: We assume SP1/Groth16 cryptographic soundness\\n\\n  ## Critical Assumption: Capture-to-Sign Integrity\\n\\n  :::warning\\n  The SDK signs the photo immediately after capture, but there is no cryptographic binding\\n  between the camera hardware and the signing operation. We assume no malicious code can\\n  execute between the moment the photo is captured and when it is signed.\\n  :::\\n\\n  This assumption holds if:\\n  - The SDK code has not been tampered with\\n  - The host application does not inject code into the capture flow\\n  - The device is not compromised\\n\\n  This is an **operational security** assumption, not a cryptographic guarantee.\\n\\n  ## Open Issues\\n\\n  ### App Trust Model\\n\\n  Currently, the SP1 program verifies that a photo was signed by *an* Apple Attested key,\\n  but does not restrict *which* apps are trusted. A malicious app could:\\n\\n  1. Integrate the SDK\\n  2. Feed AI-generated images to the signing flow\\n  3. Generate valid proofs for inauthentic photos\\n\\n  **Mitigations under consideration:**\\n  - Maintain a whitelist of trusted App IDs verified in the proof\\n  - Output the App ID as a public value, allowing verifiers to check trust\\n  - Require app attestation/audit before whitelist inclusion\\n\\n  ### Third-Party SDK Integration\\n\\n  As the SDK scales to third-party apps, we need mechanisms to ensure integrators\\n  use the SDK as intended. Options include:\\n  - Code signing / integrity checks on the SDK binary\\n  - Runtime attestation of the SDK version\\n  - Legal/contractual requirements for integrators\\n\\n  ### SDK Code Integrity\\n\\n  We need to guarantee the SDK code cannot be tampered with:\\n  - **Build pipeline**: CI/CD must produce reproducible, auditable builds\\n  - **On-device**: The SDK binary should be verified before execution\\n  - **Updates**: SDK updates must be authenticated\\n\\n  This is not yet fully implemented.\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#security\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#security\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Security\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#security-claims\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>A verified zphoto provides the following guarantees:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Device Authenticity</strong>: The photo was signed on a genuine Apple device with a Secure Enclave</li>\\n<li><strong>App Binding</strong>: The signing key is bound to a specific application via Apple App Attest</li>\\n<li><strong>Content Integrity</strong>: The photo has not been modified since the signature was created</li>\\n<li><strong>Proof Validity</strong>: The above properties are verified in a zero-knowledge proof that chains to Apple&#x27;s root certificate</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#security-claims\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nA verified zphoto provides the following guarantees:\\n\\nDevice Authenticity: The photo was signed on a genuine Apple device with a Secure Enclave\\nApp Binding: The signing key is bound to a specific application via Apple App Attest\\nContent Integrity: The photo has not been modified since the signature was created\\nProof Validity: The above properties are verified in a zero-knowledge proof that chains to Apple&#x27;s root certificate\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Security Claims\",\"titles\":[\"Security\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#trust-assumptions\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The security of ZCAM relies on the following assumptions:</p>\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Assumption</th><th>Rationale</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Secure Enclave keys cannot be exfiltrated</td><td>Hardware security guarantee from Apple</td></tr><tr><td>Apple App Attest is honest</td><td>Apple signs attestations only for legitimate device/app pairs</td></tr><tr><td>SP1 proof system is sound</td><td>Groth16 proofs cannot be forged without the witness</td></tr><tr><td>SDK code integrity</td><td>The SDK code on-device has not been tampered with</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#trust-assumptions\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe security of ZCAM relies on the following assumptions:\\nAssumptionRationaleSecure Enclave keys cannot be exfiltratedHardware security guarantee from AppleApple App Attest is honestApple signs attestations only for legitimate device/app pairsSP1 proof system is soundGroth16 proofs cannot be forged without the witnessSDK code integrityThe SDK code on-device has not been tampered with\\n\",\"title\":\"Trust Assumptions\",\"titles\":[\"Security\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#threat-model\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#threat-model\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Threat Model\",\"titles\":[\"Security\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#in-scope\",\"html\":\"\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>AI-generated images</strong>: Attacker attempts to prove a synthetic image as authentic</li>\\n<li><strong>Edited photos</strong>: Attacker modifies a photo after capture and claims it&#x27;s original</li>\\n<li><strong>Replay attacks</strong>: Attacker reuses attestation/assertion from a different photo</li>\\n<li><strong>Malicious third-party apps</strong>: An app using the SDK attempts to sign non-camera images</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#in-scope\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nAI-generated images: Attacker attempts to prove a synthetic image as authentic\\nEdited photos: Attacker modifies a photo after capture and claims it&#x27;s original\\nReplay attacks: Attacker reuses attestation/assertion from a different photo\\nMalicious third-party apps: An app using the SDK attempts to sign non-camera images\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"In Scope\",\"titles\":[\"Security\",\"Threat Model\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#out-of-scope\",\"html\":\"\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Compromised device</strong>: Jailbroken devices or hardware attacks on Secure Enclave</li>\\n<li><strong>Apple as adversary</strong>: We trust Apple&#x27;s attestation service</li>\\n<li><strong>Proof system attacks</strong>: We assume SP1/Groth16 cryptographic soundness</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#out-of-scope\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nCompromised device: Jailbroken devices or hardware attacks on Secure Enclave\\nApple as adversary: We trust Apple&#x27;s attestation service\\nProof system attacks: We assume SP1/Groth16 cryptographic soundness\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Out of Scope\",\"titles\":[\"Security\",\"Threat Model\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#critical-assumption-capture-to-sign-integrity\",\"html\":\"\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"warning\\\"><p>The SDK signs the photo immediately after capture, but there is no cryptographic binding\\nbetween the camera hardware and the signing operation. We assume no malicious code can\\nexecute between the moment the photo is captured and when it is signed.</p></aside>\\n<p>This assumption holds if:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>The SDK code has not been tampered with</li>\\n<li>The host application does not inject code into the capture flow</li>\\n<li>The device is not compromised</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>This is an <strong>operational security</strong> assumption, not a cryptographic guarantee.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#critical-assumption-capture-to-sign-integrity\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe SDK signs the photo immediately after capture, but there is no cryptographic binding\\nbetween the camera hardware and the signing operation. We assume no malicious code can\\nexecute between the moment the photo is captured and when it is signed.\\nThis assumption holds if:\\n\\nThe SDK code has not been tampered with\\nThe host application does not inject code into the capture flow\\nThe device is not compromised\\n\\nThis is an operational security assumption, not a cryptographic guarantee.\\n\",\"title\":\"Critical Assumption: Capture-to-Sign Integrity\",\"titles\":[\"Security\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#open-issues\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#open-issues\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Open Issues\",\"titles\":[\"Security\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#app-trust-model\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Currently, the SP1 program verifies that a photo was signed by <em>an</em> Apple Attested key,\\nbut does not restrict <em>which</em> apps are trusted. A malicious app could:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Integrate the SDK</li>\\n<li>Feed AI-generated images to the signing flow</li>\\n<li>Generate valid proofs for inauthentic photos</li>\\n</ol>\\n<strong>Mitigations under consideration:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Maintain a whitelist of trusted App IDs verified in the proof</li>\\n<li>Output the App ID as a public value, allowing verifiers to check trust</li>\\n<li>Require app attestation/audit before whitelist inclusion</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#app-trust-model\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nCurrently, the SP1 program verifies that a photo was signed by an Apple Attested key,\\nbut does not restrict which apps are trusted. A malicious app could:\\n\\nIntegrate the SDK\\nFeed AI-generated images to the signing flow\\nGenerate valid proofs for inauthentic photos\\n\\nMitigations under consideration:\\n\\nMaintain a whitelist of trusted App IDs verified in the proof\\nOutput the App ID as a public value, allowing verifiers to check trust\\nRequire app attestation/audit before whitelist inclusion\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"App Trust Model\",\"titles\":[\"Security\",\"Open Issues\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#third-party-sdk-integration\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>As the SDK scales to third-party apps, we need mechanisms to ensure integrators\\nuse the SDK as intended. Options include:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Code signing / integrity checks on the SDK binary</li>\\n<li>Runtime attestation of the SDK version</li>\\n<li>Legal/contractual requirements for integrators</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#third-party-sdk-integration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAs the SDK scales to third-party apps, we need mechanisms to ensure integrators\\nuse the SDK as intended. Options include:\\n\\nCode signing / integrity checks on the SDK binary\\nRuntime attestation of the SDK version\\nLegal/contractual requirements for integrators\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Third-Party SDK Integration\",\"titles\":[\"Security\",\"Open Issues\"]},{\"href\":\"/technical-docs/security#sdk-code-integrity\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>We need to guarantee the SDK code cannot be tampered with:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Build pipeline</strong>: CI/CD must produce reproducible, auditable builds</li>\\n<li><strong>On-device</strong>: The SDK binary should be verified before execution</li>\\n<li><strong>Updates</strong>: SDK updates must be authenticated</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>This is not yet fully implemented.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/technical-docs/security.mdx#sdk-code-integrity\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nWe need to guarantee the SDK code cannot be tampered with:\\n\\nBuild pipeline: CI/CD must produce reproducible, auditable builds\\nOn-device: The SDK binary should be verified before execution\\nUpdates: SDK updates must be authenticated\\n\\nThis is not yet fully implemented.\",\"title\":\"SDK Code Integrity\",\"titles\":[\"Security\",\"Open Issues\"]}]}}"
